INSERT INTO `cats` (`id`, `name`, `origin`, `history`, `characteristics`, `breed_standard`, `personality`, `image`, `description`) VALUES
(1, 'Maine Coon', 'The Maine Coon originated in the state of Maine, United States. It is one of the oldest natural cat breeds in North America. \r\n    Because of the cold climate in Maine, the breed developed thick fur, large paws, and a bushy tail to help survive harsh winters.', 'The Maine Coon developed naturally in the northeastern United States. Several legends explain its origins, including stories that it descended from long-haired cats brought by sailors or cats owned by Marie Antoinette, though these stories are not proven.\r\n\r\nWhat is known is that long-haired cats likely arrived with European seafarers in the 1700s–1800s, and over time they adapted to the cold climate of Maine. Farmers valued them for their excellent hunting abilities, especially for controlling rodents.\r\n\r\nBy the late 1800s, Maine Coons were popular in early American cat shows. \r\nHowever, their popularity declined when other long-haired breeds, such as Persians, were introduced. \r\nInterest in the breed revived in the mid-20th century, and today the Maine Coon is one of the most popular cat breeds in the world.', 'The Maine Coon is known for its large size and strong, rugged appearance. It has a long, muscular body with a broad chest and sturdy bone structure. One of its most noticeable features is its large ears, which are wide at the base and often have tufted tips that resemble those of a lynx. Its eyes are large and expressive, commonly appearing in shades of green, gold, or copper. The Maine Coon also has a long, thick, and water-resistant coat, which helps protect it from cold weather. Around the neck, the fur forms a thick ruff that gives the cat a majestic look. Another distinctive feature is its very long, bushy tail, which is often almost as long as its body. Maine Coons can come in a wide variety of colors and patterns, including tabby, solid, and tortoiseshell.', 'Size - One of the largest domestic cat breeds; males are usually larger than females.\r\nBody - Long, muscular body with a broad chest and strong bones.\r\nHead - Slightly longer than wide with high cheekbones.\r\nEars - Large, wide at the base, often with lynx-like tufts at the tips.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive; colors vary (green, gold, copper, sometimes blue).\r\nCoat - Long, thick, and water-resistant with a ruff of fur around the neck.\r\nTail - Very long and bushy, almost as long as the body.\r\nColors - Can appear in many colors and patterns, including tabby, solid, and tortoiseshell.', 'Maine Coons are often called “gentle giants” because of their large size combined with their friendly and affectionate nature. They are known to be very intelligent and curious cats, often learning tricks or games and enjoying interactive play. Despite their size, they remain playful even as adults and like spending time with their owners. Maine Coons are sociable but not overly demanding of attention, making them easy companions in many households. They usually get along well with children and other pets. Because of their loyal and interactive behavior, they are sometimes described as dog-like, often following their owners around the house. Instead of loud meows, they usually communicate with soft chirping or trilling sounds.', 'mainecoon.jpg', 'Famous for their large size, bushy tail, and gentle “gentle giant” personality.'),
(2, 'Abyssinian Cat', 'The Abyssinian cat is often called the “ancient cat” because of its striking resemblance to the felines depicted in Egyptian art. While its exact origin is debated, many believe it traces back to regions near the Indian Ocean, possibly brought to Europe by traders.\r\n', 'The breed gained popularity in the late 19th century in England after being exhibited at early cat shows. Despite disruptions during wartime, dedicated breeders revived and refined the Abyssinian, making it one of the most beloved and recognizable short-haired cats today.', 'Abyssinians are known for their sleek, athletic bodies and their unique “ticked” coat, where each hair has multiple bands of color. Their almond-shaped eyes and large ears give them a constantly alert and curious expression, making them look as lively as they truly are.', 'Size - Medium-sized cat; males are slightly larger than females.\r\nBody - Slim, elegant, and muscular with a graceful posture.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped with smooth contours and a slightly rounded skull.\r\nEars - Large, wide at the base, and alert-looking.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped and expressive; colors include gold, green, or hazel.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and ticked with multiple color bands on each hair.\r\nTail - Long, tapering, and proportionate to the body.\r\nColors - Ruddy, red, blue, and fawn are most common.', 'Highly energetic and intelligent, Abyssinians thrive on interaction and play. They love climbing, exploring, and being involved in everything their humans do. If you’re looking for a quiet lap cat, this isn’t it—but if you want a playful companion full of personality, the Abyssinian is a perfect match.', 'Abyssinian Cat.jpg', 'Known for their short ticked coat, active personality, and strong curiosity.'),
(4, ' American Bobtail', 'The American Bobtail is a distinctly North American breed, easily recognized by its naturally short, “bobbed” tail. It developed in the United States and is often admired for its rugged, wildcat-like appearance.', 'The breed began in the 1960s when a short-tailed kitten was found and bred with domestic cats. Over time, breeders focused on preserving the unique tail and enhancing the breed’s hardy and adaptable traits, leading to the American Bobtail we know today.', 'American Bobtails have a sturdy, muscular build and can come in both short- and long-haired varieties. Their tails are short but expressive, and their overall look often resembles a miniature lynx, adding to their wild charm.', 'Size - Medium to large; males are typically bigger and heavier.\r\nBody - Stocky, muscular, and well-built with a solid frame.\r\nHead - Broad and slightly wedge-shaped with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Medium-sized with slightly rounded tips.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped and can come in various colors.\r\nCoat - Can be short or long; slightly shaggy and dense.\r\nTail - Naturally short, ranging from one-third to half the length of a normal tail.\r\nColors - Found in almost all colors and patterns.', 'Despite their wild looks, American Bobtails are gentle, affectionate, and incredibly adaptable. They form strong bonds with their families and are known to be playful without being overly demanding. Many even enjoy interactive games and can adapt well to travel, earning them a reputation as easygoing companions.\r\n', 'American Bobtail Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their short “bobbed” tail and dog-like loyalty.'),
(5, 'American Curl', 'The American Curl stands out for its uniquely curled-back ears, a natural genetic mutation first discovered in California in the 1980s. This charming feature quickly captured the hearts of cat lovers.', 'The breed began with a stray cat named Shulamith, whose unusual ears became the foundation of the American Curl line. Breeders carefully developed the breed while maintaining its distinctive look and ensuring good health and temperament.', 'American Curls are medium-sized cats with silky coats that can be either short or long. Their most defining trait is their ears, which curl backward in a graceful arc, giving them a perpetually surprised and endearing expression.', 'Size - Medium-sized with a balanced build.\r\nBody - Slim, flexible, and moderately muscular.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped with soft curves.\r\nEars - Distinctively curled backward, giving a unique appearance.\r\nEyes - Walnut-shaped and expressive; available in many colors.\r\nCoat - Soft, silky, and can be short or long.\r\nTail - Long and graceful, often plumed in longhaired varieties.\r\nColors - Wide variety of colors and patterns.', 'Friendly, playful, and people-oriented, American Curls are often described as “cats with a kitten-like personality that never fades.” They enjoy being around their humans, adapt well to different environments, and are known for their gentle and affectionate nature—perfect for families and first-time cat owners.', 'American Curl Cat.jpg', 'Famous for their unique ears that curl backward and their friendly nature.'),
(6, 'American Shorthair', ' The American Shorthair traces its roots back to early European settlers who brought cats to North America to protect food supplies from rodents. Over time, these hardworking cats evolved into a strong and adaptable breed.', ' Originally known as domestic shorthairs, selective breeding in the early 20th century helped refine their appearance and temperament. They were officially recognized as the American Shorthair to distinguish them from non-pedigreed cats.', ' American Shorthairs are known for their sturdy build, round faces, and dense coats. They come in a wide range of colors and patterns, with the silver tabby being especially popular and eye-catching.', 'BREED STANDARD\r\nSize - Medium to large; males are usually heavier.\r\nBody - Strong, muscular, and well-proportioned.\r\nHead - Round with full cheeks and a broad muzzle.\r\nEars - Medium-sized with slightly rounded tips.\r\nEyes - Large and round; commonly gold, green, or copper.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, and thick.\r\nTail - Medium-length with a slightly rounded tip.\r\nColors - Silver tabby is popular, along with many other colors and patterns.', ' These cats are calm, easygoing, and independent yet affectionate. They enjoy companionship without being overly demanding, making them ideal for families, working individuals, or first-time cat owners.', 'American Shorthair Cat.webp', 'Known for their sturdy build, calm temperament, and excellent hunting skills.'),
(7, 'American Wirehair', ' The American Wirehair is a rare and uniquely textured breed that originated in the United States due to a natural genetic mutation.', ' First discovered in a farm kitten in New York in the 1960s, breeders preserved the unusual wiry coat through careful breeding. Despite its rarity, it has gained admiration for its distinct look and hardy nature.', ' What sets this breed apart is its coarse, springy coat, including even the whiskers, which are often curled or crimped. They have a similar body type to the American Shorthair but with a more unusual texture.', 'Size - Medium-sized and well-balanced.\r\nBody - Muscular and sturdy with a firm build.\r\nHead - Rounded with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and set well apart.\r\nEyes - Round and bright; colors vary.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, and uniquely wiry or crimped.\r\nTail - Medium in length and proportionate.\r\nColors - Wide range of colors and patterns.', ' American Wirehairs are affectionate, playful, and adaptable. They enjoy interactive play but also appreciate quiet time, making them a great balance between energetic and relaxed companions.', 'American Wirehair Cat.jpg', 'Identified by their unusual wiry coat and relaxed personality.'),
(8, 'Arabian Mau', 'The Arabian Mau originates from the deserts of the Middle East, where it developed naturally as a survivalist breed adapted to harsh climates.', ' Unlike many breeds, the Arabian Mau was not created through selective breeding but evolved naturally over centuries. It was only recently recognized as a formal breed due to its unique traits and regional importance.', ' Arabian Maus are lean, agile, and built for endurance. Their short coat helps them tolerate heat, and their alert eyes and strong limbs reflect their desert heritage.', 'Size - Medium-sized; lean and agile.\r\nBody - Slim, athletic, and built for endurance.\r\nHead - Slightly rounded with defined cheekbones.\r\nEars - Large and upright.\r\nEyes - Oval-shaped and expressive; usually green or yellow.\r\nCoat - Short, smooth, and close-lying.\r\nTail - Medium-length and slightly tapered.\r\nColors - White, black, tabby, and bicolor variations.', 'Highly active and intelligent, Arabian Maus are independent but can form strong bonds with their owners. They are curious explorers who enjoy space to roam and play, making them perfect for active households.', 'arabian mau.png', 'Known for being highly adaptable, energetic, and well suited to hot climates.'),
(9, 'Asian Cat', 'The Asian cat was developed in the United Kingdom and is closely related to the Burmese, sharing its elegant body and expressive eyes.', ' The breed emerged in the 1980s when breeders crossed Burmese cats with other breeds, resulting in a group of cats with similar body types but a wide variety of coat colors and patterns.', ' Asian cats are sleek and medium-sized with glossy coats. Their diversity in color—from solid shades to tabby and even smoky patterns—makes each one uniquely beautiful.', 'Size - Medium-sized with a refined appearance.\r\nBody - Elegant, muscular, and well-balanced.\r\nHead - Rounded wedge with soft contours.\r\nEars - Medium to large and slightly rounded.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive; typically yellow or green.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and glossy.\r\nTail - Medium to long and tapering.\r\nColors - Comes in a wide variety of colors and patterns.', ' These cats are affectionate, social, and highly interactive. They thrive on attention and enjoy being part of family activities, often following their owners from room to room.', 'Asian Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their sleek body, expressive eyes, and affectionate personality.'),
(10, 'Australian Mist', 'The Australian Mist is the first cat breed developed in Australia, specifically bred to be a perfect indoor companion.', ' Created in the 1970s by crossing Burmese, Abyssinian, and domestic cats, the breed was designed to have a friendly temperament and a beautifully patterned coat. It was originally called the Spotted Mist before expanding to include marbled patterns.', ' Australian Mists have soft, short coats with a delicate “misty” pattern that gives them their name. Their gentle expression and balanced build add to their charm.', 'Size - Medium-sized and moderately built.\r\nBody - Muscular yet soft and rounded.\r\nHead - Broad and gently rounded.\r\nEars - Medium-sized with rounded tips.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive; usually green.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, and smooth.\r\nTail - Medium-length and balanced.\r\nColors - Spotted or marbled patterns with a misty overlay.\r\n', 'Friendly, gentle, and highly adaptable, Australian Mists are ideal indoor pets. They are great with children and other animals, and their calm, affectionate nature makes them a joy to have in any home.\r\n', 'Australian Mist Cat.jpg', 'Known for their spotted or marbled coat and gentle, family-friendly nature.'),
(11, 'Balinese Cat', ' The Balinese cat originated in the United States and is essentially a long-haired variety of the Siamese. Its elegant appearance and flowing coat give it a graceful, almost dancer-like presence—hence the name inspired by Balinese dancers.', ' The breed developed in the mid-20th century when long-haired kittens began appearing in Siamese litters. Instead of being dismissed, breeders embraced this unique trait and refined it into a distinct and recognized breed.', ' Balinese cats are slender and elegant with silky, medium-length coats that lack a heavy undercoat. Their striking blue eyes and color-point patterns make them look both refined and eye-catching.', 'Size - Medium-sized; males are slightly larger.\r\nBody - Slender, elegant, and fine-boned.\r\nHead - Long, wedge-shaped with a straight profile.\r\nEars - Large, pointed, and set wide apart.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped and vivid blue.\r\nCoat - Long, silky, and flowing without an undercoat.\r\nTail - Long and plumed with silky fur.\r\nColors - Colorpoint patterns such as seal, blue, chocolate, and lilac.', ' Balinese cats are highly intelligent, vocal, and affectionate. They love interacting with their humans and are known to “talk” often, making them perfect companions for those who enjoy an expressive and social pet.', 'Balinese Cat.jpg', 'Known for their silky coat, elegant body, and talkative personality.'),
(12, 'Bambino Cat', ' The Bambino cat is a relatively new and rare breed created by crossing the hairless Sphynx with the short-legged Munchkin, resulting in a unique and eye-catching appearance.', ' Developed in the early 2000s, the Bambino was bred to combine the playful personality of the Sphynx with the distinctive stature of the Munchkin. Its name means “baby” in Italian, reflecting its cute and youthful look.', ' Bambino cats are small, with short legs and little to no fur. Their wrinkled skin, large ears, and wide eyes give them an almost otherworldly charm.', 'Size - Small to medium; compact and low to the ground.\r\nBody - Muscular with short legs and a sturdy frame.\r\nHead - Rounded with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Large and upright.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and expressive.\r\nCoat - Hairless or nearly hairless with soft skin.\r\nTail - Long, whip-like, and flexible.\r\nColors - Various skin tones and patterns.', ' Despite their unusual appearance, Bambinos are lively, affectionate, and extremely people-oriented. They love attention, enjoy playtime, and often seek warmth and cuddles from their owners.', 'bambino.jpg', 'Recognized for their hairless body, short legs, and playful behavior.'),
(13, 'Bengal Cat', ' The Bengal cat was developed by crossing domestic cats with the Asian leopard cat, giving it a stunning wild appearance with a domestic personality.', ' The breed was refined in the late 20th century, with breeders focusing on maintaining the exotic look while ensuring a friendly and manageable temperament.', 'Their patterns resemble those of wild cats, making them one of the most visually striking breeds.', 'Size - Medium to large; males are typically larger and more muscular.\r\nBody - Strong, athletic, and sleek with a wild appearance.\r\nHead - Broad with a slightly rounded wedge shape.\r\nEars - Small to medium with rounded tips.\r\nEyes - Oval and striking; usually green or gold.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, and luxurious with a glittery sheen.\r\nTail - Thick, medium-length with a rounded tip.\r\nColors - Spotted or marbled patterns, often resembling a leopard.', ' Energetic and curious, Bengals love climbing, exploring, and playing. They are intelligent and often enjoy interactive toys or even learning tricks, making them ideal for active households.', 'Bengal-cat.jpg', 'Famous for their leopard-like spotted coat and energetic, adventurous nature.'),
(14, 'Birman', ' The Birman is often referred to as the “Sacred Cat of Burma,” with origins tied to legends of temple cats in Southeast Asia.', 'Though its exact origins are surrounded by myth, the Birman was developed and standardized in France in the early 20th century, becoming known for its beauty and gentle nature.', ' Birmans are medium to large cats with silky coats, deep blue eyes, and distinctive white “gloves” on their paws. Their color-point pattern adds to their elegant appearance.', 'Size - Medium to large with a solid build.\r\nBody - Stocky, muscular, and well-balanced.\r\nHead - Broad and rounded with gentle contours.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and slightly rounded.\r\nEyes - Deep blue and expressive.\r\nCoat - Long, silky, and soft with minimal matting.\r\nTail - Long and plumed.\r\nColors - Colorpoint with distinctive white “gloves” on the paws.', ' Birmans are affectionate, gentle, and sociable. They enjoy being around people but are not overly demanding, making them wonderful companions for quiet and loving homes.', 'Birman Cat.png', 'Known for their striking blue eyes, silky coat, and gentle temperament.'),
(15, 'Bombay Cat', ' The Bombay cat was developed in the United States to resemble a miniature black panther, combining elegance with a sleek, glossy coat.', ' Created in the 1950s by crossing Burmese cats with black American Shorthairs, the breed was carefully developed to achieve its signature all-black appearance and striking golden eyes.', ' Bombay cats have a muscular yet compact body, short black coats that shine like patent leather, and expressive copper or gold eyes.', 'Size - Medium-sized; males are slightly larger and heavier.\r\nBody - Muscular, compact, and well-balanced.\r\nHead - Rounded with a strong muzzle and prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Medium-sized, rounded at the tips, set well apart.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and striking; usually copper or gold.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and glossy, lying close to the body.\r\nTail - Medium-length, thick at the base, tapering slightly at the tip.\r\nColors - Jet black is standard.', 'Bombays are affectionate, playful, and love being the center of attention. They often form strong bonds with their owners and enjoy both playtime and cuddling, making them a perfect mix of fun and companionship.', 'bombay.jpg', 'Recognized for their sleek black coat and bright copper eyes.'),
(16, 'British Longhair', ' The British Longhair developed in the United Kingdom as a long-haired variant of the British Shorthair, combining classic charm with a more luxurious coat.', ' This breed emerged when British Shorthairs were crossed with Persian cats to enhance coat length and density. Over time, breeders stabilized its traits, resulting in a distinct breed with a plush, flowing appearance.', ' British Longhairs are known for their dense, fluffy coats and round faces that give them a soft, teddy bear-like look. Their calm expression and sturdy build add to their overall appeal.', 'Size - Medium to large; sturdy and solid.\r\nBody - Stocky, muscular, and well-proportioned.\r\nHead - Rounded with full cheeks and a broad muzzle.\r\nEars - Small to medium, rounded at the tips.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and expressive; typically copper or gold.\r\nCoat - Long, dense, and plush with a soft undercoat.\r\nTail - Medium to long, bushy, and rounded at the tip.\r\nColors - Many colors and patterns, including blue, black, and tabby.', ' These cats are gentle, calm, and affectionate without being overly demanding. They enjoy quiet companionship and are perfect for relaxed households.', 'British Longhair.png', 'Known for their plush long coat and calm, affectionate personality.'),
(17, 'British Shorthair', ' The British Shorthair is one of the oldest English cat breeds, believed to descend from cats brought to Britain by the Romans.', ' Over centuries, the breed developed into a strong and hardy cat. It became especially popular in the Victorian era and remains one of the most iconic breeds today.', ' With their round faces, chubby cheeks, and dense coats, British Shorthairs have a distinctly plush and cuddly appearance. The blue-gray variety is particularly famous.', 'Size - Medium to large; males are usually heavier.\r\nBody - Cobby, muscular, and broad-chested.\r\nHead - Round with full cheeks and a strong jawline.\r\nEars - Small to medium, rounded at the tips.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and expressive; most commonly copper or gold.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, and plush with a crisp texture.\r\nTail - Medium-length, thick, and rounded at the tip.\r\nColors - Blue is classic, but many other colors and patterns exist.', ' British Shorthairs are calm, easygoing, and independent. They enjoy being around people but are not overly clingy, making them ideal companions for a balanced lifestyle.', 'British-shorthair-cat-.jpg', 'Famous for their round face, dense coat, and easygoing nature.'),
(18, 'Burmese Cat', ' The Burmese cat originated from Southeast Asia and was later developed into a distinct breed in the United States and Europe.', ' The modern Burmese breed traces back to a single cat named Wong Mau, brought from Burma in the 1930s. Breeding programs refined its appearance and friendly temperament.', ' Burmese cats have sleek, muscular bodies and short, glossy coats. Their expressive eyes and warm coat colors give them a lively and inviting look.', 'Size - Medium-sized; muscular yet compact.\r\nBody - Strong, muscular, and elegant with a rounded chest.\r\nHead - Rounded with a short muzzle and pronounced cheekbones.\r\nEars - Medium, slightly rounded, and set wide apart.\r\nEyes - Large, expressive, and typically golden or yellow.\r\nCoat - Short, glossy, and close-lying.\r\nTail - Medium-length, tapering to a rounded tip.\r\nColors - Sable, champagne, blue, and platinum.', ' Burmese cats are affectionate, playful, and highly social. They crave attention and enjoy being involved in their owners’ daily activities, making them lively and loving companions.', 'Burmese Cat.jpg', 'Known for their sleek coat, expressive eyes, and affectionate personality.'),
(19, 'Burmilla', ' The Burmilla was accidentally created in the United Kingdom from a cross between a Burmese and a Chinchilla Persian.', ' The breed began in the 1980s when an unexpected mating produced kittens with a unique silver coat. Their beauty and charm quickly led to the development of a new breed.', ' Burmillas are known for their shimmering, silver-tipped coats and expressive green eyes. Their elegant yet sturdy build gives them a graceful appearance.', 'Size - Medium; females slightly smaller than males.\r\nBody - Elegant, muscular, and balanced.\r\nHead - Rounded with a gentle wedge shape.\r\nEars - Medium-sized, slightly rounded at the tips.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive; usually green.\r\nCoat - Short to semi-long, soft, and silky with a shimmering effect.\r\nTail - Medium-length, proportionate, and slightly rounded at the tip.\r\nColors - Silver shaded is standard, with others possible in breeding.', ' These cats are affectionate, playful, and gentle. They strike a perfect balance between energy and relaxation, making them wonderful companions for many types of homes.', 'Burmilla Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their shimmering silver coat and playful temperament.'),
(20, 'Chartreux', ' The Chartreux is a rare and ancient breed from France, known for its quiet nature and striking blue-gray coat.', ' Legend has it that Chartreux cats were kept by monks for their hunting skills. Over time, they became treasured companions and were carefully preserved as a distinct breed.', ' Chartreux cats have a robust build, woolly blue coat, and copper or gold eyes. Their subtle smiles and gentle expressions give them a uniquely charming appearance.', 'Size - Medium to large; sturdy and strong.\r\nBody - Muscular, compact, and well-rounded.\r\nHead - Rounded with full cheeks and a slightly flattened forehead.\r\nEars - Medium, broad at the base, rounded at the tips.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and copper-colored.\r\nCoat - Short to medium, dense, and woolly.\r\nTail - Medium-length, thick at the base, tapering slightly.\r\nColors - Blue-gray is classic.', ' Chartreux cats are calm, quiet, and deeply loyal. They tend to bond closely with their owners and are known for their gentle and observant nature, making them ideal for peaceful homes.', 'Chartreux Cat.jpg', 'Known for their blue-gray coat, quiet voice, and intelligent nature.'),
(21, 'Chausie', ' The Chausie is a striking hybrid breed developed by crossing domestic cats with the wild jungle cat, giving it a bold and exotic appearance.', ' The breed was developed in the late 20th century, with breeders aiming to create a domestic cat that retained the wild look of its ancestors while having a friendly and manageable temperament.', ' Chausies are large, athletic cats with long legs, deep chests, and a powerful build. Their short coats and alert expressions highlight their wild heritage.', 'Size - Large; males are generally bigger and more muscular.\r\nBody - Long, athletic, and built for agility.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped with a straight profile.\r\nEars - Large, upright, and alert.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped; typically gold or green.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and close-lying.\r\nTail - Medium-length, thick at the base, tapering.\r\nColors - Black, brown, and spotted tabby are common.', 'Highly energetic and intelligent, Chausies need plenty of space and stimulation. They are loyal and form strong bonds but thrive best with experienced owners who can match their active lifestyle.', 'Chausie-cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their wild appearance, athletic build, and energetic personality.'),
(22, 'Cornish Rex', ' The Cornish Rex originated in Cornwall, England, and is known for its soft, wavy coat and slender body.', ' The breed began with a natural mutation in the 1950s that resulted in a curly coat. Breeders carefully developed this unique trait into the elegant Cornish Rex we know today.', 'Cornish Rex cats have a fine, curly coat that feels like velvet, along with long legs, large ears, and a slender frame. Their unique look makes them stand out instantly.', 'Size - Small to medium; males are slightly larger.\r\nBody - Slim, fine-boned, and elegant with an arched back.\r\nHead - Egg-shaped with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Very large and set high on the head.\r\nEyes - Oval-shaped and expressive.\r\nCoat - Very short, soft, and curly.\r\nTail - Long, thin, and tapering.\r\nColors - Wide variety, including solid and patterned coats.', 'Playful and mischievous, Cornish Rex cats are full of energy and love attention. They remain kitten-like well into adulthood and enjoy interactive games and human companionship.\r\n', 'Cornish-Rex-cat.jpg', 'Known for their curly coat, slender body, and playful energy.'),
(23, 'Cymric Cat', 'The Cymric cat is a long-haired version of the Manx, originating from the Isle of Man and known for its tailless or short-tailed appearance.', ' The breed developed naturally from the Manx gene mutation that affects tail length. Over time, long-haired variants were recognized as a separate breed.', ' Cymric cats have a round, sturdy body and a thick, plush coat. Their lack of a full tail gives them a distinctive and memorable silhouette.', 'Size - Medium; slightly heavier than a comparable domestic shorthair.\r\nBody - Compact, round, and muscular.\r\nHead - Round with full cheeks and a short muzzle.\r\nEars - Medium, set well apart, and rounded.\r\nEyes - Large and round; colors vary.\r\nCoat - Long, dense, and flowing without mats.\r\nTail - Naturally tailless or very short, sometimes bobbed.\r\nColors - All standard colors and patterns are accepted.', ' Cymrics are affectionate, gentle, and loyal. They are known for being playful yet calm, often forming strong bonds with their families and enjoying a cozy home environment.', 'Cymric.jpg', 'Recognized for their long coat and naturally tailless or short-tailed body.'),
(24, 'Devon Rex', ' The Devon Rex originated in Devon, England, and is famous for its pixie-like face and curly coat.', ' Discovered in the 1960s, the Devon Rex developed from a natural mutation different from that of the Cornish Rex. Breeders worked to preserve its distinct look and playful personality.', 'Devon Rex cats have large ears, high cheekbones, and soft, wavy fur. Their lightweight bodies and expressive faces give them an almost elfin appearance.', 'Size - Small; females slightly smaller than males.\r\nBody - Slim, lightweight, and muscular.\r\nHead - Pixie-like with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Very large, low-set, and wide at the base.\r\nEyes - Large, expressive, and slightly oval.\r\nCoat - Short, soft, and wavy or curly.\r\nTail - Long, thin, and tapering.\r\nColors - Wide variety including solid, tabby, and point.', 'Devon Rex cats are incredibly social, playful, and affectionate. They love being the center of attention and often seek warmth, whether from a sunny spot or their owner’s lap.', 'Devon-Rex-cat.jpg', 'Known for their wavy coat, large ears, and mischievous personality.'),
(25, 'Donskoy Cat', ' The Donskoy cat comes from Russia and is known for its hairless appearance, caused by a dominant genetic mutation.', 'The breed was discovered in the 1980s in Russia and quickly gained recognition for its unique look and resilient nature.', ' Donskoy cats can be completely hairless or have a fine fuzz. Their wrinkled skin, prominent cheekbones, and muscular build give them a distinctive and unforgettable appearance.', 'Size - Medium; males are slightly larger and more muscular.\r\nBody - Muscular, lean, and well-proportioned with a graceful appearance.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Large, upright, and slightly pointed.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped and expressive; usually gold or green.\r\nCoat - Hairless, soft, and warm to the touch; some may have a very fine fuzz.\r\nTail - Long and tapering.\r\nColors - All colors and patterns are possible on skin.', 'Friendly, intelligent, and affectionate, Donskoy cats are known for their loyalty. They enjoy human interaction and are often described as dog-like in their devotion and playfulness.', 'donskoy.jpg', 'Recognized for their hairless body and affectionate nature.'),
(26, 'Dragon Li', 'The Dragon Li, also known as the Chinese Li Hua, originates from China and is considered a naturally occurring breed with deep cultural roots.', 'This breed has existed for centuries in rural China, where it developed naturally without selective breeding. It was only recently recognized internationally, bringing attention to its unique heritage.', ' Dragon Li cats are medium-sized with a strong, muscular build and a short, dense coat featuring a distinctive tabby pattern. Their alert expression reflects their intelligence and keen hunting instincts.', 'Size - Medium; males slightly larger than females.\r\nBody - Muscular, athletic, and balanced.\r\nHead - Broad with high cheekbones and a rounded muzzle.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and upright.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped; usually green or yellow.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, and resilient.\r\nTail - Medium-length, tapering toward the tip.\r\nColors - Golden brown tabby with black markings is classic.', 'Dragon Li cats are intelligent, independent, and loyal. While they may be reserved with strangers, they form strong bonds with their owners and enjoy interactive play.', 'Dragon-Li-cat.jpg', 'Known for their naturally occurring Chinese origin and distinctive striped coat.'),
(27, 'Egyptian Mau', 'The Egyptian Mau is one of the few naturally spotted domestic cats, with origins tracing back to ancient Egypt.', ' Highly valued in ancient times, the breed nearly disappeared but was revived in the 20th century through careful breeding programs, preserving its unique spotted coat.', ' Egyptian Maus are elegant and athletic, known for their naturally occurring spots, gooseberry-green eyes, and graceful movement.', 'Size - Medium; lean and athletic with strong muscles.\r\nBody - Elegant, muscular, and built for speed.\r\nHead - Slightly wedge-shaped with a gentle curve.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and alert.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped and vivid green.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and soft with visible spots.\r\nTail - Medium-length, tapering to a pointed tip.\r\nColors - Silver, bronze, and smoke with black spotting.', ' These cats are active, playful, and deeply loyal. They often form strong attachments to their owners and are known for their sensitivity and intelligence.', 'egyptian mau.jpg', 'Famous for being one of the few naturally spotted domestic cats and for their speed.'),
(28, 'European Shorthair', 'The European Shorthair developed across Europe from natural domestic cats, making it one of the continent’s most traditional breeds.', 'Descended from cats that spread throughout Europe with the Romans, the breed was later standardized to preserve its natural look and hardy traits.', 'European Shorthairs are robust and well-balanced with short coats that come in a wide variety of colors and patterns. They have a classic, no-frills feline appearance.', 'Size - Medium; males are slightly larger.\r\nBody - Strong, muscular, and well-proportioned.\r\nHead - Rounded with a broad muzzle.\r\nEars - Medium-sized, slightly rounded at the tips.\r\nEyes - Large and round; green, gold, or copper.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, and resilient.\r\nTail - Medium-length, thick at the base, tapering slightly.\r\nColors - Wide variety, including tabby, solid, and bicolor.', ' Adaptable and independent, these cats are friendly without being overly demanding. They make excellent companions for both families and individuals.', 'European Shorthair.png', 'Known for their sturdy build and balanced, adaptable temperament.'),
(29, 'Exotic Shorthair', 'The Exotic Shorthair was developed as a short-haired version of the Persian, combining its signature look with easier coat care.', 'The breed emerged in the United States in the mid-20th century when breeders crossed Persians with American Shorthairs, eventually creating a distinct and popular breed.', 'Exotic Shorthairs have round faces, large eyes, and plush, dense coats. They are often described as “the lazy person’s Persian” due to their similar appearance with less grooming required.', 'Size - Medium; males usually slightly larger.\r\nBody - Cobby, compact, and muscular.\r\nHead - Round with a flat face and short muzzle.\r\nEars - Small, rounded, and set wide apart.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and expressive; typically copper or gold.\r\nCoat - Short, plush, and dense with a soft texture.\r\nTail - Short, thick, and rounded at the tip.\r\nColors - Wide variety, including solid, tabby, and colorpoint patterns.', 'Gentle, quiet, and affectionate, Exotic Shorthairs enjoy calm environments. They love lounging and bonding with their owners, making them perfect for relaxed households.\r\n', 'Exotic-shorthair-cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their Persian-like face but with a short, plush coat.'),
(30, 'Havana Brown', 'The Havana Brown originated in England and is known for its rich, chocolate-colored coat.', 'Developed in the 1950s, the breed was created by crossing Siamese cats with domestic black cats, resulting in its unique color and refined appearance.', 'Havana Browns are medium-sized with sleek bodies and short coats in a warm brown shade. Their striking green eyes and elegant features make them stand out.', 'Size - Medium; muscular and compact.\r\nBody - Sleek, muscular, and balanced.\r\nHead - Longer wedge-shaped with a slightly rounded muzzle.\r\nEars - Large, broad at the base, and set wide apart.\r\nEyes - Large, oval, and green.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and glossy.\r\nTail - Medium-length, tapering slightly.\r\nColors - Rich chocolate brown is standard.', 'Havana Browns are affectionate, curious, and playful. They enjoy interacting with people and are known for their charming and social nature.', 'havana-brown.jpg', 'Known for their rich chocolate-brown coat and bright green eyes.'),
(31, 'Highlander Cat', 'The Highlander cat originated in the United States and was developed to resemble a wild cat while maintaining a fully domestic and friendly nature.', 'This relatively new breed was created in the early 2000s by crossing desert lynx–type cats with other domestic breeds. Breeders focused on enhancing its distinctive curled ears and bobbed tail.', 'Highlander cats are muscular and athletic, often with curled ears and short tails. Their wild appearance is paired with a playful and approachable look.', 'Size - Medium to large; males usually larger than females.\r\nBody - Muscular, athletic, and strong-boned.\r\nHead - Broad with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Medium to large, sometimes curled at tips.\r\nEyes - Oval-shaped; colors vary.\r\nCoat - Short or long, dense, and soft.\r\nTail - Medium-length or bobbed depending on variety.\r\nColors - Wide range including spotted, marbled, and solid.', 'Highlanders are energetic, playful, and highly social. They enjoy interactive games and are known for their dog-like behavior, often following their owners and even learning tricks.', 'Highlander Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their curled ears, bobbed tail, and playful personality.'),
(32, 'Himalayan Cat', 'The Himalayan cat was developed by crossing Persian and Siamese cats, combining the best features of both breeds.', 'The breed was established in the mid-20th century, with breeders aiming to achieve the Persian’s luxurious coat along with the Siamese’s striking color-point pattern.', 'Himalayan cats have long, thick coats, round faces, and vivid blue eyes. Their color-point markings give them a dramatic and elegant look.', 'Size - Medium to large; males generally heavier.\r\nBody - Cobby, muscular, and sturdy.\r\nHead - Round with a flat face and short muzzle.\r\nEars - Small, rounded, and set wide apart.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and vivid blue.\r\nCoat - Long, thick, and plush with an undercoat.\r\nTail - Long, bushy, and balanced with the body.\r\nColors - Colorpoint patterns: seal, blue, chocolate, lilac, and more.', 'Himalayans are gentle, calm, and affectionate. They enjoy quiet environments and close companionship, making them perfect for relaxed homes.', 'HIMALAYAN-CAT.jpg', 'Known for their long coat, blue eyes, and color-point pattern.'),
(33, 'Japanese Bobtail', 'The Japanese Bobtail comes from Japan and has been part of the country’s culture and folklore for centuries.', 'Often associated with good luck and prosperity, this breed has long been depicted in Japanese art and is believed to inspire the famous “beckoning cat” figurine.', 'Japanese Bobtails are slender and elegant, with a distinctive short, pom-pom-like tail. They often have silky coats and expressive, oval eyes.\r\n', 'Size - Medium; slender and athletic.\r\nBody - Graceful, muscular, and agile.\r\nHead - Triangular with a slightly rounded forehead.\r\nEars - Large, upright, and alert.\r\nEyes - Oval-shaped; colors vary depending on coat.\r\nCoat - Short or long, soft, and fine.\r\nTail - Distinctively short, “pom-pom” shaped.\r\nColors - Calico, bicolor, and other standard Japanese colors.', 'These cats are lively, intelligent, and affectionate. They are very social and enjoy interacting with people, often “talking” with soft, chirping sounds.', 'Japanese-Bobtail-cat.jpg', 'Famous for their short pom-pom tail and lively, friendly personality.'),
(34, 'Khao Manee', 'The Khao Manee, also known as the “White Gem” of Thailand, comes from the royal courts of Siam (modern-day Thailand). Revered for centuries, it was considered a sacred and lucky cat, often kept by royalty for its beauty and elegance.', 'This breed has a long-standing history in Thailand, mentioned in ancient manuscripts and folklore as a symbol of purity and good fortune. Despite its royal roots, the Khao Manee gradually spread outside of Thailand and is now cherished worldwide for its striking appearance and gentle nature.', 'Khao Manees are medium-sized cats with a sleek, muscular build. Their coat is pure white and short, giving them a pristine, elegant look. One of their most distinctive features is their eyes: they can be blue, gold, or even odd-eyed (one blue, one gold), which adds an extra touch of magic to their appearance.', 'Size - Medium; lean and elegant.\r\nBody - Slender, muscular, and balanced.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped with smooth contours.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and upright.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive; can be blue, gold, or odd-eyed.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and glossy.\r\nTail - Medium-length and tapering.\r\nColors - Pure white is standard.', 'Khao Manees are intelligent, affectionate, and curious. They enjoy attention and form close bonds with their families but are not overly demanding. Known for their gentle demeanor and playful streak, they make excellent companions for households that appreciate a calm yet engaging cat.', 'khao manee.jpg', 'Known for their pure white coat and striking odd-colored eyes.'),
(35, 'Korat', 'The Korat originated in Thailand, where it is considered one of the country’s most ancient and sacred cat breeds. It developed naturally in the region and is often associated with good fortune, prosperity, and protection. Because of Thailand’s tropical climate, the Korat evolved a short, sleek coat that helps regulate body temperature.', 'The Korat is mentioned in ancient Thai manuscripts called the Tamra Maew, which date back to the 14th century. Traditionally, these cats were not sold but given as gifts during special occasions such as weddings, symbolizing luck and happiness.\r\nThe breed remained rare outside Thailand until the 1950s, when it was introduced to the United States. Breeders worked carefully to preserve its natural traits. Today, the Korat is still considered a symbol of good luck in its homeland and remains a relatively rare but cherished breed worldwide.\r\n', 'The Korat is a medium-sized cat with a muscular and compact body. It has a distinctive heart-shaped face with a broad forehead and strong chin. One of its most striking features is its large, luminous green eyes, which stand out against its silver-blue coat. The coat is short, fine, and lies close to the body, with silver-tipped hairs that create a shimmering effect. Its ears are large and alert, and its tail is medium in length, tapering slightly at the end.', 'Size - Medium-sized with a compact and muscular build.\r\nBody - Semi-cobby, strong, and well-balanced.\r\nHead - Distinct heart shape with a broad forehead.\r\nEars - Large, wide at the base, and alert.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and bright green.\r\nCoat - Short, fine, and silver-blue with a glossy sheen.\r\nTail - Medium length, tapering toward the tip.\r\nColors - Solid silver-blue only.\r\n', 'Korats are highly intelligent and deeply affectionate cats that form strong bonds with their owners. They are known for their loyalty and often prefer to stay close to their favorite person. While they enjoy play and interaction, they are generally quiet and sensitive, preferring calm environments. Korats can be shy around strangers but are loving and devoted within the household. They are also observant and alert, making them excellent companions for those who want a gentle yet attentive pet.', 'Korat Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their silver-blue coat and heart-shaped face.'),
(36, 'LaPerm', 'The LaPerm originated in the United States, specifically in the state of Oregon. It began as a natural genetic mutation in a farm cat population, resulting in kittens with curly or wavy coats. Because it developed in a rural environment, the breed adapted well to different conditions. Its unique coat and hardy nature are the result of this spontaneous mutation rather than planned breeding, making the LaPerm a naturally occurring and distinctive cat breed.', 'The LaPerm breed began in 1982 when a barn cat gave birth to a kitten with no fur, which later grew into a soft, curly coat. This unique trait was passed on to future generations, leading to the development of the breed.\r\n\r\nBreeders recognized the uniqueness of the curly coat and began selective breeding programs. The LaPerm was officially recognized in the late 20th century and has since gained popularity for its unusual appearance and affectionate nature.\r\n', 'The LaPerm is known for its soft, curly or wavy coat, which can vary from loose waves to tight ringlets. It has a slender yet muscular body and a wedge-shaped head with large, expressive eyes. Its ears are medium to large and slightly flared. The coat can come in a wide variety of colors and patterns, and its texture is light and airy rather than dense.', 'Size - Medium-sized with a slender body.\r\nBody - Lean but muscular.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped with soft contours.\r\nEars - Medium to large, slightly flared.\r\nEyes - Large, expressive, and almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Curly or wavy, soft and light.\r\nTail - Plumed with curls.\r\nColors - Wide range of colors and patterns.\r\n', 'LaPerms are affectionate, playful, and people-oriented cats that enjoy being around humans. They are curious and intelligent, often exploring their surroundings and interacting with their environment. These cats are known for their gentle nature and adaptability, making them suitable for families and individuals alike. They enjoy attention but are not overly demanding, and they tend to form strong bonds with their owners.', 'LaPerm.jpg', 'Known for their curly coat and affectionate personality.'),
(37, 'Lykoi Cat', 'The Lykoi originated in the United States from a naturally occurring genetic mutation found in domestic shorthair cats. This mutation results in a partially hairless coat, giving the breed its distinctive appearance.', 'The Lykoi breed was first discovered in 2010 when breeders identified cats with unusual, patchy coats. After confirming that the mutation was not related to existing hairless breeds, a selective breeding program was established.\r\n\r\nThe breed quickly gained attention due to its unique “werewolf-like” appearance. It has since been recognized by cat associations and continues to develop as a rare and distinctive breed.\r\n', 'The Lykoi has a striking appearance with a sparse, patchy coat and a mix of colored and white hairs, known as a roan pattern. Its face often appears partially hairless, especially around the eyes and muzzle. It has a medium-sized, lean body, large ears, and bright, expressive eyes. Despite its unusual look, it is a healthy and active cat.\r\n', 'Size - Medium-sized with a lean build.\r\nBody - Slender and muscular.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped with a slightly hairless face.\r\nEars - Large and upright.\r\nEyes - Medium to large, expressive.\r\nCoat - Sparse, patchy, roan-patterned.\r\nTail - Medium length.\r\nColors - Typically black roan.', 'Lykoi cats are playful, curious, and highly intelligent. They are often described as having dog-like behavior, enjoying interactive play and forming strong bonds with their owners. They are energetic and enjoy exploring but also appreciate companionship. Despite their wild appearance, they are friendly and affectionate pets that adapt well to home environments.', 'Lykoi Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their sparse “werewolf-like” coat and curious nature.');
INSERT INTO `cats` (`id`, `name`, `origin`, `history`, `characteristics`, `breed_standard`, `personality`, `image`, `description`) VALUES
(38, 'Manx Cat', 'The Manx Cat originated on the Isle of Man, a small island in the Irish Sea. It developed naturally in this isolated environment, where a genetic mutation caused the breed’s distinctive taillessness.', 'The Manx is one of the oldest known cat breeds, with its tailless trait believed to have appeared centuries ago. Because of the island’s isolation, this genetic mutation became common among the local cat population.\r\n\r\nOver time, the Manx gained popularity beyond the Isle of Man and became recognized for its unique appearance. It was one of the early breeds exhibited in cat shows during the 19th century and remains well-known today.', 'The Manx is a medium-sized cat with a rounded, compact body and strong hind legs that are longer than the front legs. This gives it a distinctive, slightly arched back. Its head is round with full cheeks and large eyes. The most notable feature is its lack of a tail or the presence of a very short tail. It has a dense double coat that can be either short or long.', 'Size - Medium-sized and sturdy.\r\nBody - Compact with a rounded appearance.\r\nHead - Round with full cheeks.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and slightly rounded.\r\nEyes - Large and round.\r\nCoat - Dense double coat (short or long).\r\nTail - Absent or very short.\r\nLegs - Hind legs longer than front legs.\r\n', 'Manx cats are intelligent, playful, and loyal companions. They are known for their strong hunting instincts and quick reflexes. These cats often form close bonds with their families and can be protective of their home. They enjoy interactive play and can adapt well to different living environments. Manx cats are generally friendly and get along well with children and other pets.', 'Manx Cat.jpg', 'Known for their naturally tailless body and strong hind legs.'),
(39, 'Minskin', 'The Minskin originated in the United States and is a relatively new breed developed through selective breeding. It was created to combine the short legs of the Munchkin with the hairless traits of the Sphynx.', 'The breed was first developed in the late 1990s by breeder Paul McSorley in Boston. By crossing Munchkin, Sphynx, and other breeds, he aimed to create a cat with short legs and minimal fur. The Minskin remains a rare breed and is still being developed. It has gained attention for its unique appearance and friendly personality.', 'The Minskin is a small cat with short legs and a compact body. It has sparse fur, usually concentrated on the face, ears, legs, and tail, while the body may be nearly hairless. Its head is rounded with large ears and expressive eyes. The skin is soft and warm to the touch.', 'Size - Small and compact.\r\nBody - Low to the ground with short legs.\r\nHead - Rounded with prominent cheekbones.\r\nEars - Large and open.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive.\r\nCoat - Sparse fur with hairless areas.\r\nTail - Medium length.\r\nSkin - Soft and warm.', 'Minskins are friendly, playful, and affectionate cats that enjoy human companionship. They are curious and energetic despite their small size and short legs. These cats are social and adapt well to different households, often getting along with children and other pets. They are known for their gentle and loving nature.', 'minskin.jpg', 'Recognized for their short legs, sparse coat, and affectionate temperament.'),
(40, 'Munchkin Cat', 'The Munchkin Cat originated in the United States and is known for its naturally occurring genetic mutation that causes short legs. Despite this trait, the breed developed as a healthy and active domestic cat.', 'Short-legged cats have been reported throughout history, but the modern Munchkin breed was established in the 1980s. A cat named Blackberry, discovered in Louisiana, became the foundation of the breed. Breeders worked to develop the Munchkin while maintaining overall health and normal cat behavior. The breed gained recognition in the 1990s and continues to be popular today.', 'The Munchkin has a normal-sized body but noticeably short legs. It has a rounded head, medium-sized ears, and bright, expressive eyes. Its coat can be short or long and comes in a wide variety of colors and patterns. Despite its short stature, it is agile and active.', 'Size - Small to medium-sized.\r\nBody - Medium build with short legs.\r\nHead - Rounded with soft contours.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and upright.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive.\r\nCoat - Short or long, various colors.\r\nTail - Medium length.\r\nLegs - Distinctly short.\r\n', 'Munchkin cats are playful, outgoing, and energetic. They are known for their curiosity and love of exploring their surroundings. Despite their short legs, they are surprisingly agile and enjoy running and playing. They are affectionate and social, often forming strong bonds with their owners and getting along well with other pets.', 'Munchkin Cat.jpg', 'Known for their short legs and playful personality.'),
(41, 'Napoleon Cat (Minuet)', 'The Napoleon Cat, also known as the Minuet, originated in the United States. It was developed by crossing Persian cats with Munchkin cats, combining the Persian’s luxurious coat with the Munchkin’s short legs.', 'The breed was first developed in the 1990s with the goal of creating a cat that had both the Persian’s sweet expression and the Munchkin’s unique stature. Over time, breeders refined the breed to ensure good health and balanced features. The name “Minuet” was later adopted by some cat associations, and the breed continues to grow in popularity.', 'The Napoleon Cat has a round face, large expressive eyes, and a compact body. It may have short legs like the Munchkin or standard-length legs. Its coat is soft and plush, ranging from short to long, and comes in many colors and patterns.', 'Size - Small to medium-sized.\r\nBody - Compact and well-rounded.\r\nHead - Round with full cheeks.\r\nEars - Small to medium-sized, rounded tips.\r\nEyes - Large, round, and expressive.\r\nCoat - Short or long, soft and plush.\r\nTail - Medium length and fluffy.\r\nLegs - Short or standard length.\r\n', 'Napoleon cats are affectionate, gentle, and friendly. They enjoy being around people and are known for their sweet and calm nature. These cats are playful but not overly active, making them suitable for various households. They tend to get along well with children and other pets and form strong bonds with their families.', 'napolean cat.jpg', 'Known for their short legs, round face, and sweet temperament.'),
(42, 'Norwegian Forest Cat', 'The Norwegian Forest Cat originated in Norway, where it developed naturally in cold forest environments. Its thick coat and sturdy body helped it survive harsh Scandinavian winters.', 'This breed has existed for centuries and is even mentioned in Norse mythology and folklore. It is believed that these cats were companions to Vikings and lived in rural farms and forests. The breed was officially recognized in the 20th century after efforts were made to preserve it. Today, it is one of Norway’s most beloved native cat breeds.', 'The Norwegian Forest Cat is a large, strong cat with a long, dense double coat. It has a triangular head, almond-shaped eyes, and large ears, often with tufts. Its bushy tail and thick fur protect it from cold climates.', 'Size - Large and robust.\r\nBody - Strong and muscular.\r\nHead - Triangular shape.\r\nEars - Large with tufted tips.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Long, thick double coat.\r\nTail - Long and bushy.\r\nLegs - Strong and sturdy.', 'Norwegian Forest Cats are independent yet affectionate. They enjoy human companionship but do not demand constant attention. They are intelligent, playful, and adaptable, making them good family pets. These cats are also known for their climbing abilities and love of exploring.', 'Norwegian Forest Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their thick water-resistant coat and strong climbing ability.'),
(43, 'Ocicat', 'The Ocicat originated in the United States and was developed through selective breeding of Siamese, Abyssinian, and American Shorthair cats.', 'The breed was accidentally created in the 1960s when breeders attempted to produce a Siamese with Abyssinian markings. The resulting spotted kitten resembled a wild ocelot, leading to the name “Ocicat.” The breed was further developed and officially recognized for its wild appearance and domestic temperament.', 'he Ocicat is a muscular, athletic cat with a short, smooth coat covered in distinct spots. It has a broad chest, strong legs, and a sleek body. Its eyes are large and almond-shaped, and its ears are alert.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Muscular and athletic.\r\nHead - Slightly wedge-shaped.\r\nEars - Medium-sized and alert.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Short, smooth, and spotted.\r\nTail - Medium to long.\r\nColors - Various spotted patterns.', 'Ocicats are outgoing, social, and energetic. They enjoy interacting with people and are often described as dog-like in behavior. They are intelligent and can be trained to play games or follow commands. These cats thrive in active households and enjoy companionship.', 'Ocicat Cat.jpg', 'Known for their wild-looking spotted coat but friendly domestic personality.'),
(44, 'Oriental Shorthair', 'The Oriental Shorthair originated in the United Kingdom and the United States. It was developed from the Siamese breed to create a cat with similar body type but a wider variety of coat colors.', 'Breeders in the mid-20th century worked to expand the color range of Siamese cats by crossing them with other breeds. This led to the development of the Oriental Shorthair. The breed was officially recognized and has since become popular for its sleek appearance and wide variety of colors.', 'The Oriental Shorthair has a slender, elegant body with long legs and a long tail. It has a wedge-shaped head, large ears, and almond-shaped eyes. Its coat is short, smooth, and comes in many colors and patterns.', 'Size - Medium-sized and slender.\r\nBody - Long and elegant.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped.\r\nEars - Very large and wide.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Short and smooth.\r\nTail - Long and thin.\r\nColors - Wide variety of colors and patterns.', 'Oriental Shorthairs are highly social, vocal, and intelligent. They enjoy being the center of attention and form strong bonds with their owners. These cats are playful and curious, often exploring their surroundings and engaging in interactive play.', 'oriental shorthair.png', 'Recognized for their sleek body, large ears, and wide variety of coat colors.'),
(45, 'Persian Cat', 'The Persian Cat originated in Persia, which is modern-day Iran. It is one of the oldest and most well-known cat breeds in the world.', 'Persian cats were brought to Europe in the 1600s and quickly became popular among royalty and nobility. Over time, selective breeding emphasized their long coats and flat faces. The breed became one of the most popular in cat shows and remains widely recognized today.', 'The Persian Cat has a long, luxurious coat and a round face with a short nose. It has a stocky body, large eyes, and small ears. Its coat requires regular grooming to maintain its appearance.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Stocky and compact.\r\nHead - Round with a short nose.\r\nEars - Small and rounded.\r\nEyes - Large and round.\r\nCoat - Long and dense.\r\nTail - Short and fluffy.\r\nColors - Wide range of colors.', 'Persian cats are calm, gentle, and affectionate. They prefer quiet environments and enjoy relaxing rather than active play. These cats are loving companions and form strong bonds with their owners, making them ideal for peaceful households.', 'Persian cat.jpg', 'Known for their long, fluffy fur and sweet temperament.'),
(46, 'Peterbald', 'The Peterbald originated in Russia and is a relatively modern breed developed in St. Petersburg.', 'he breed was created in the 1990s by crossing the Donskoy (a hairless breed) with the Oriental Shorthair. The goal was to produce a sleek, elegant cat with varying coat types. The Peterbald quickly gained recognition for its unique appearance and affectionate personality.', 'The Peterbald has a slender body, long limbs, and a wedge-shaped head. It may be completely hairless or have a fine coat. Its ears are large, and its eyes are almond-shaped.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Slender and elegant.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped.\r\nEars - Large and wide.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Hairless or fine coat.\r\nTail - Long and thin.\r\nSkin - Soft and warm.', 'Peterbalds are affectionate, social, and intelligent cats. They enjoy being around people and are known for their friendly and outgoing nature. These cats are active and playful but also enjoy relaxing with their owners.', 'Peterbald Cat.jpg', 'Recognized for their hairless or fine coat and elegant slender body.'),
(47, 'Pixie-bob', ' The Pixie-bob originated in the United States and was developed to resemble the North American bobcat.', 'The breed was developed in the 1980s through selective breeding of domestic cats with bobbed tails. Despite their wild appearance, they are fully domestic cats. The Pixie-bob gained recognition for its unique look and gentle temperament.', 'The Pixie-bob is a medium to large cat with a muscular build and a short, bobbed tail. It often has a spotted coat and a rugged appearance.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Muscular and sturdy.\r\nHead - Broad with strong jaw.\r\nEars - Medium-sized.\r\nEyes - Hooded appearance.\r\nCoat - Short or long, often spotted.\r\nTail - Short or bobbed.\r\nLegs - Strong and sturdy.', 'Pixie-bobs are loyal, calm, and affectionate. They are often described as dog-like due to their loyalty and ability to learn commands. They enjoy companionship and are generally good with families.', 'Pixiebob Cat.jpg', 'Known for their bobbed tail, spotted coat, and wild bobcat-like appearance.'),
(48, 'Ragamuffin Cat', 'The Ragamuffin originated in the United States and was developed from the Ragdoll breed.', 'The breed was established in the 1990s when breeders wanted to expand the color range and features of the Ragdoll. It has since become recognized as a distinct breed known for its plush coat and gentle nature.', 'The Ragamuffin has a large, soft body with a thick, plush coat. It has a round head, large eyes, and a sweet expression.', 'Size - Large.\r\nBody - Broad and heavy.\r\nHead - Rounded.\r\nEars - Medium-sized.\r\nEyes - Large and expressive.\r\nCoat - Medium-long and plush.\r\nTail - Full and fluffy.\r\nColors - Wide variety.', 'Ragamuffins are gentle, affectionate, and calm. They enjoy being held and spending time with their owners. These cats are friendly and adaptable, making them excellent family pets.', 'ragamuffin.png', 'Known for their plush coat and calm, affectionate personality.'),
(49, 'Ragdoll', 'The Ragdoll originated in California, United States, and was developed in the 1960s.', 'he breed was created by breeder Ann Baker, who selected cats with calm temperaments and striking blue eyes. Ragdolls became popular for their relaxed nature and unique tendency to go limp when picked up.', 'Ragdolls are large cats with semi-long coats and bright blue eyes. They have a soft, silky coat and a colorpoint pattern.', 'Size - Large.\r\nBody - Long and muscular.\r\nHead - Broad and rounded.\r\nEars - Medium-sized.\r\nEyes - Blue and oval.\r\nCoat - Semi-long and soft.\r\nTail - Long and fluffy.\r\nPattern - Colorpoint.\r\n', 'Ragdolls are gentle, calm, and affectionate. They enjoy being held and are known for their relaxed behavior. They are friendly and social, often following their owners around.', 'Chat ragdoll_ caractéristiques et photos.jpg', 'Famous for their blue eyes and tendency to go limp when held.'),
(50, 'Russian Blue', 'The Russian Blue originated in northern Russia, where it adapted to cold climates.', 'The breed was brought to Europe by sailors and became popular in cat shows. It has remained known for its elegant appearance and calm nature.', 'The Russian Blue has a short, dense blue-gray coat and bright green eyes. It has a slender, graceful body.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Slender and graceful.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped.\r\nEars - Large.\r\nEyes - Green.\r\nCoat - Short, dense, blue-gray.\r\nTail - Medium length.\r\nTexture - Plush and soft.\r\n', 'Russian Blues are quiet, gentle, and intelligent. They can be shy with strangers but are affectionate with their families.', 'Russian blue.jpg', 'Recognized for their dense blue-gray coat and bright green eyes.'),
(51, 'Savannah Cat', 'The Savannah Cat originated in the United States and is a hybrid between a domestic cat and a serval.', ' The first Savannah was bred in the 1980s, combining wild and domestic traits. The breed gained recognition for its exotic appearance and active nature.', ' The Savannah is tall and lean with long legs and a spotted coat. It resembles a wild cat.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Tall and lean.\r\nHead - Small relative to body.\r\nEars - Large and upright.\r\nEyes - Medium-sized.\r\nCoat - Short and spotted.\r\nTail - Medium length.\r\nLegs - Long.\r\n', 'Savannah cats are active, intelligent, and adventurous. They require stimulation and enjoy interactive play.', 'Savannah Cat.jpg', 'Known for their tall, slender build and wild serval-like appearance.'),
(52, 'Scottish Fold', 'The Scottish Fold originated in Scotland and is known for its unique folded ears.', 'The breed began in the 1960s with a cat named Susie, who had naturally folded ears. Selective breeding preserved this trait, making the breed widely recognized.', 'Scottish Folds have round faces, large eyes, and folded ears.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Rounded and sturdy.\r\nHead - Round.\r\nEars - Folded forward.\r\nEyes - Large and round.\r\nCoat - Short or long.\r\nTail - Medium length.\r\nTexture - Soft and dense.', 'Scottish Folds are gentle, affectionate, and calm. They enjoy companionship and are easygoing pets.', 'Scottish Fold Cat.jpg', 'Famous for their folded ears and round face.'),
(53, 'Selkirk Rex', 'The Selkirk Rex originated in the United States.', 'It was developed from a naturally curly-coated cat discovered in the 1980s. The breed was established through selective breeding.', 'The Selkirk Rex has a curly coat and a sturdy body.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Muscular.\r\nHead - Round.\r\nEars - Medium-sized.\r\nEyes - Large.\r\nCoat - Curly and dense.\r\nTail - Medium length.\r\nTexture - Plush curls.\r\n', 'Selkirk Rex cats are calm, friendly, and tolerant. They are affectionate and good with families.', 'Selkirk Rex.jpg', 'Recognized for their thick curly coat and relaxed personality.'),
(54, 'Siamese Cat', 'The Siamese Cat originated in Thailand, formerly known as Siam. It is one of the oldest and most recognizable cat breeds in the world.', 'Siamese cats were kept by royalty and monks in ancient Thailand. They were later introduced to Europe in the 19th century. The breed became popular worldwide due to its unique appearance and vocal personality.', 'The Siamese has a slender body, blue eyes, and a colorpoint coat.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Slender and elegant.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped.\r\nEars - Large.\r\nEyes - Blue and almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Short and fine.\r\nTail - Long and thin.\r\nPattern - Colorpoint.\r\n', 'Siamese cats are vocal, affectionate, and highly social. They enjoy interaction and attention.', 'siamese.jpg', 'Known for their color-point coat, blue eyes, and vocal personality.'),
(55, 'Siberian Cat', 'The Siberian Cat originated in Russia and developed naturally in cold climates.', 'It is an ancient breed mentioned in Russian folklore. The breed became internationally recognized in the late 20th century.', 'The Siberian has a thick triple coat and a strong body.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Muscular.\r\nHead - Rounded.\r\nEars - Medium-sized.\r\nEyes - Slightly oval.\r\nCoat - Triple-layered.\r\nTail - Bushy.\r\nTexture - Dense.', 'Siberians are playful, affectionate, and intelligent. They are good family pets.', 'Siberian.jpg', 'Recognized for their thick triple coat and strong, athletic body.'),
(56, 'Singapura Cat', 'The Singapura originated in Singapore and is one of the smallest cat breeds.', ' It developed from street cats in Singapore and was later introduced to the United States. The breed gained recognition for its small size and unique appearance.', 'The Singapura has a small body, large eyes, and a ticked coat.', 'Size - Small.\r\nBody - Petite.\r\nHead - Rounded.\r\nEars - Large.\r\nEyes - Large.\r\nCoat - Short and ticked.\r\nTail - Short to medium.\r\nTexture - Fine.', 'Singapuras are playful, curious, and affectionate. They enjoy attention and interaction.', 'Singapurski.jpg', 'Known for being one of the smallest cat breeds and their large expressive eyes.'),
(57, 'Snowshoe Cat', 'The Snowshoe originated in the United States.', 'It was developed from Siamese cats with white markings. The breed became recognized for its unique appearance.', 'The Snowshoe has white paws and a colorpoint coat.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Balanced.\r\nHead - Slightly rounded.\r\nEars - Medium.\r\nEyes - Blue.\r\nCoat - Short.\r\nMarkings - White feet.\r\nPattern - Colorpoint.', 'Snowshoes are friendly, social, and vocal. They enjoy companionship.', 'Snowshoe.jpg', 'Recognized for their white “snow-boot” paws and color-point pattern.'),
(58, 'Sokoke', 'The Sokoke originated in Kenya, specifically the Sokoke Forest.', 'It developed naturally and was later introduced to Europe. The breed remains rare.', 'The Sokoke has a marbled coat and slender body.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Slender.\r\nHead - Small.\r\nEars - Large.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Short and marbled.\r\nTail - Long.\r\nLegs - Long.\r\n', 'Sokokes are active, intelligent, and independent.', 'sokoke.png', 'Known for their rare African origin and distinctive marbled coat.'),
(59, 'Sphynx Cat', 'The Sphynx originated in Canada from a natural hairless mutation.', 'The breed was developed through selective breeding in the 1960s. It became popular for its unique appearance.', 'The Sphynx is hairless with wrinkled skin.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Muscular.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped.\r\nEars - Large.\r\nEyes - Lemon-shaped.\r\nCoat - Hairless.\r\nSkin - Wrinkled.\r\nTail - Long.', 'Sphynx cats are affectionate, energetic, and social.', 'Sphynx.jpg', 'Famous for their hairless body and affectionate personality.'),
(60, 'Thai Cat', 'The Thai Cat originated in Thailand, formerly known as Siam, and represents the traditional or “old-style” Siamese cat. It developed naturally in the region and was well-suited to the tropical climate, with a short coat that helps regulate body temperature. The breed retains the original appearance of early Siamese cats before modern breeding created a more slender type.', 'The Thai Cat has ancient roots and is mentioned in historical Thai manuscripts such as the Tamra Maew, which date back several centuries. These cats were highly valued and often kept by royalty and monks, symbolizing good fortune and protection.\r\n\r\nIn the late 19th century, Siamese cats were brought to Europe, where selective breeding eventually led to the modern Siamese. However, some breeders worked to preserve the original, more moderate type, which became known as the Thai Cat. Today, it is recognized as a separate breed that maintains the traditional Siamese look.', 'The Thai Cat has a balanced, medium-sized body with a more rounded appearance compared to the modern Siamese. It has a gently rounded head, full cheeks, and a shorter, less extreme muzzle. Its eyes are large, expressive, and always blue. The coat is short, smooth, and lies close to the body, featuring the classic colorpoint pattern where the ears, face, paws, and tail are darker than the body.', 'Size - Medium-sized with a balanced build.\r\nBody - Moderately muscular and well-proportioned.\r\nHead - Rounded with soft contours and full cheeks.\r\nEars - Medium-sized with slightly rounded tips.\r\nEyes - Large, round to slightly oval, always blue.\r\nCoat - Short, smooth, and close-lying.\r\nTail - Medium length, tapering slightly.\r\nPattern - Colorpoint (seal, blue, chocolate, lilac, etc.).', 'Thai Cats are affectionate, social, and highly intelligent. They form strong bonds with their owners and enjoy being involved in daily activities. Like their Siamese relatives, they are vocal and communicative, often expressing themselves with a variety of sounds. They are playful and curious, maintaining their energy even into adulthood. Thai Cats thrive on companionship and do best in environments where they receive plenty of attention and interaction.', 'Thai Cat.jpg', 'Known for their traditional Siamese appearance and social personality.'),
(61, 'Tonkinese Cat', 'The Tonkinese originated in North America.', 'It was developed by crossing Siamese and Burmese cats. The breed combines traits from both.', 'The Tonkinese has a moderate build and a mink coat pattern.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Muscular.\r\nHead - Rounded wedge.\r\nEars - Medium.\r\nEyes - Aqua.\r\nCoat - Short.\r\nPattern - Mink.\r\nTexture - Smooth.', 'Tonkinese cats are playful, social, and affectionate.', 'Tonkinese.jpg', 'Recognized for their silky coat and playful, affectionate nature.'),
(62, 'Toyger', 'The Toyger originated in the United States.', 'It was developed to resemble a miniature tiger. The breed is relatively new.', 'The Toyger has bold stripes and a muscular body.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Muscular.\r\nHead - Rounded.\r\nEars - Small.\r\nEyes - Medium.\r\nCoat - Short and striped.\r\nTail - Long.\r\nPattern - Tiger-like stripes.\r\n', 'Toygers are friendly, intelligent, and active.', 'toyger.png', 'Known for their tiger-like striped coat and muscular build.'),
(63, 'Turkish Angora', ' The Turkish Angora originated in Turkey.', ' It is one of the oldest natural breeds. It was prized in royal courts.', ' The breed has a long, silky coat and elegant body.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Slender.\r\nHead - Small.\r\nEars - Large.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Long and silky.\r\nTail - Plumed.\r\nBuild - Fine-boned.\r\n', 'Turkish Angoras are playful, intelligent, and affectionate.', 'turkish angora.png', 'Recognized for their silky coat and graceful, elegant body.'),
(64, 'Turkish Van', ' The Turkish Van originated in the Lake Van region of Turkey.', ' It developed naturally in the region. It is known for its love of water.', ' The Turkish Van has a semi-long coat and distinct markings.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Muscular.\r\nHead - Wedge-shaped.\r\nEars - Medium.\r\nEyes - Large.\r\nCoat - Semi-long.\r\nPattern - Van pattern.\r\nTail - Bushy.', 'Turkish Vans are energetic, playful, and independent.', 'Turkish Van.jpg', 'Known for their semi-long coat and love of swimming.'),
(65, 'Ukrainian Levkoy', ' The Ukrainian Levkoy originated in Ukraine.', ' It was developed by crossing hairless and fold-eared cats. The breed is relatively new.', ' It is hairless with folded ears and an angular body.', 'Size - Medium-sized.\r\nBody - Slender.\r\nHead - Angular.\r\nEars - Folded.\r\nEyes - Almond-shaped.\r\nCoat - Hairless.\r\nSkin - Wrinkled.\r\nTail - Long.\r\n', 'Ukrainian Levkoys are friendly, social, and affectionate.', 'Ukrainian Levkoy Cat.jpg', 'Known for their hairless body, inward-folding ears, and affectionate, dog-like personality.'),
(66, 'York Chocolate', ' The York Chocolate originated in New York, United States. It developed naturally from farm cats and was later selectively bred for its distinctive chocolate-colored coat.', ' The breed began in the 1980s when a farm cat produced kittens with rich brown coats. A breeder recognized this unique trait and began developing the York Chocolate. Although it gained some recognition, the breed remains relatively rare today.', 'The York Chocolate is a medium to large cat with a long, soft coat in shades of chocolate or lavender. It has a well-proportioned body, bright eyes, and a bushy tail. Its coat is smooth and slightly glossy.', 'Size - Medium to large.\r\nBody - Well-proportioned and muscular.\r\nHead - Rounded with gentle contours.\r\nEars - Medium-sized.\r\nEyes - Bright and expressive.\r\nCoat - Long and soft.\r\nTail - Full and bushy.\r\nColors - Chocolate or lavender.', 'York Chocolate cats are gentle, affectionate, and friendly. They enjoy human companionship and are known for their calm and loving nature. These cats adapt well to home environments and form strong bonds with their families.', 'york chocolate.jpg', 'Recognized for their long, silky chocolate-colored coat and gentle, friendly temperament.');
